The paper deals with epistemic logic programs, which are a type of knowledge representation and reasoning in artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the semantics of these programs, which falls under cs.LO (logic in computer science) and cs.PL (programming languages). The paper also mentions conformant planning, which is a subfield of automated planning and scheduling, falling under cs.CL (computational linguistics) and cs.AI. Finally, the paper discusses epistemic constraints, which are a type of constraint programming, falling under cs.DL (digital libraries) and cs.AI.
